The paper deals with the design of space-time block codes for broadcasting common information in a massive MIMO downlink. This involves the use of channel-independent precoding and joint design of precoding matrix and signal constellation. These concepts are related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer communication (cs.COM).
